The paper discusses the design of next-generation cellular networks for massive machine-type communication, which involves aspects of networking, information theory, security, and system engineering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses protocols, techniques, and energy efficiency, which are relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper addresses security challenges, which are relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
